main event: A solid octagonal shaped object, silver in color, was observed at Snelling AFB for approximately 5 hours.
interesting points: The object was surrounded by binoculars and was the size of a cigarette end when viewed without them,It appeared stationary during the observation period,The report suggests that the object may have emitted light from its bottom sides,An observer described the object as having a well-defined octagonal plane surface,Dr. Robinson concluded that the sighting was probably a balloon.
witness description: a reliable weather officer and his wife and two boys
